name: awesome-go
description: A curated list of awesome Go frameworks, libraries and software

name: terraform
description: Terraform enables you to safely and predictably create, change, and improve infrastructure. It is an open source tool that codifies APIs into declarative configuration files that can be shared amongst team members, treated as code, edited, reviewed, and versioned.

name: istio
description: Connect, secure, control, and observe services.

name: seaweedfs
description: SeaweedFS is a fast distributed storage system for blobs, objects, files, and data lake, for billions of files! Blob store has O(1) disk seek, cloud tiering. Filer supports Cloud Drive, cross-DC active-active replication, Kubernetes, POSIX FUSE mount, S3 API, S3 Gateway, Hadoop, WebDAV, encryption, Erasure Coding.

name: kops
description: Kubernetes Operations (kOps) - Production Grade k8s Installation, Upgrades and Management

name: ingress-nginx
description: Ingress-NGINX Controller for Kubernetes

name: casbin
description: An authorization library that supports access control models like ACL, RBAC, ABAC in Golang

name: containerd
description: An open and reliable container runtime

name: tinygo
description: Go compiler for small places. Microcontrollers, WebAssembly (WASM/WASI), and command-line tools. Based on LLVM.

name: thanos
description: Highly available Prometheus setup with long term storage capabilities. A CNCF Incubating project.

name: runc
description: CLI tool for spawning and running containers according to the OCI specification

name: cert-manager
description: Automatically provision and manage TLS certificates in Kubernetes

name: katana
description: A next-generation crawling and spidering framework.

name: keda
description: KEDA is a Kubernetes-based Event Driven Autoscaling component. It provides event driven scale for any container running in Kubernetes

name: sealed-secrets
description: A Kubernetes controller and tool for one-way encrypted Secrets

name: sliver
description: Adversary Emulation Framework

name: kubevela
description: The Modern Application Platform.

name: livekit
description: End-to-end stack for WebRTC. SFU media server and SDKs.

name: aws-nuke
description: Nuke a whole AWS account and delete all its resources.

name: coder
description: A tool that provisions remote development environments via Terraform

name: volcano
description: A Cloud Native Batch System (Project under CNCF)

name: cloudnative-pg
description: CloudNativePG is a Kubernetes operator that covers the full lifecycle of a PostgreSQL database cluster with a primary/standby architecture, using native streaming replication

name: junodb
description: JunoDB is PayPal's home-grown secure, consistent and highly available key-value store providing low, single digit millisecond, latency at any scale.

name: vault-secrets-operator
description: The Vault Secrets Operator (VSO) allows Pods to consume Vault secrets natively from Kubernetes Secrets.
